did.head: Overview
did.abstract: Collection contains his professional papers pertaining to his teaching and research, including syllabi and other class materials, notes, lectures, correspondence, articles, and illustrations; the research files pertain to the skeletal system. There are also several files pertaining to Physicians for Social Responsibility.

prefercite.head: Cite As
prefercite.p: Henry H. Jones Papers (SC0859). Department of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical Sketch
bioghist.p: Professor Emeritus of radiology, Stanford School of Medicine. Jones earned his BA in chemistry at Haverford College in 1939 and his MD from Yale. After several years as an instructor at the Army School of Roentgenology, he joined the faculty at the Stanford School of Medicine in 1948 and taught until his retirement in 2006. Jones was a founding member of Physicians for Social Responsibility.

scopecontent.head: Description of the Collection
scopecontent.p: Collection contains his professional papers pertaining to his teaching and research, including syllabi and other class materials, notes, lectures, correspondence, articles, and illustrations; the research files pertain to the skeletal system. There are also several files pertaining to Physicians for Social Responsibility.
